- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is likely because the paper focuses on parallelism and improving the speed of decompression.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is likely because the paper discusses the limitations of the DEFLATE compression algorithm and the difficulty of decompressing files at arbitrary locations.
- cs.DB (Databases) is possible because the paper discusses the problem of random access to compressed data, which is relevant to database systems.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is possible because the paper proposes a new implementation of the gzip decompression algorithm.
